d 'BOUNDEDUROOT': module to perform unit-root and level-shift tests for bounded time series 
d
d	boundeduroot is a library of unit-root and level-shift
d tests for bounded time series - series confined to an interval
d either    by construction or by policy (unemployment rates,
d budget shares, nominal interest rates, capacity-utilisation
d rates,    target-zone exchange rates). It is the structural-break
d companion to the base command boundedur, which implements the   
d Cavaliere & Xu (2014) simulation-based ADF and M tests. Where
d boundedur handles the no-break case, boundeduroot adds GLS   
d detrending, structural breaks in the mean, and multiple
d level-shift detection, each with bound-specific critical values  
d  obtained by simulating a regulated (reflected) Brownian motion. 
d
d KW: unit root tests
d KW: level shift
d KW: structural breaks
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260707
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
f boundeduroot.ado
f boundeduroot.sthlp
f boundeduroot_breaks.ado
f boundeduroot_breaks.sthlp
f boundeduroot_examples.do
f boundeduroot_hlt.ado
f boundeduroot_hlt.sthlp
f boundeduroot_mtests.ado
f boundeduroot_mtests.sthlp
f boundeduroot_selftest.do
